postcontent: Another rare, highly collectible beauty from my personal collection… an excellent condition COP, Inc. Compact off-Duty Police 4 barrel Derringer chambered for the .357 Magnum and .38 Special cartridges. This very well made and robust firearm was manufactured between 1983 and 1990 by now defunct COP Inc. of Torrance, California. The COP .357 was not the first 4 barrel, pepperbox-style derringer, however none had ever fired anything like .357 Magnum before. The COP .357 is an all stainless steel, double action only, tip-forward barrel derringer. It has 4 barrels and four firing pins which are triggered sequentially. The overall finish, grips and the 4 bores are in excellent condition. It comes with its blue factory hard case only. If you have ever desired a nice COP .357 in this condition, you have found it... don’t let this opportunity pass

title: For Sale:  STAINLESS RECEIVER RIFLE
postcontent: How would you like to have ONE rifle that does it all? From prairie dogs to elk, even combat if necessary. The 308 cartridge has proven to be an inherently very accurate and hard hitting round. With modern powders it rivals the ubiquitous 30-06. Fewer cartridges are more versatile than the 308 while still maintaining light recoil. It is available worldwide and at every Walmart. This rifle is unique in that it can chamber rounds longer than industry standard like the M118LR; all the way to 2.850" in the mag. It is possible to mount a folding stock on this rifle if necessary. The barrel length is the ultimate compromise between portability and long range performance. There is no op rod to bend like an M1A. No gas adjuster needed for different loads or when dirty like the F.A.L. Having been impressed with modern semiautomatic rifles' accuracy like the AR15 approaching bolt action performance but allowing faster follow up shots; I went on a quest to learn all I could with this platform. First 223/5.56mm, then 308 winchester and finally the 6.8mm SPC. Because of the versatility of the 308 winchester and the severe wind in Wyoming; I settled on the 308 cartridge to keep logistics simple. Having been disappointed with the lack of reliability in my AR10 clone, and having seen firsthand how incredibly reliable an AK47 can be; I started to wonder if it were possible to have a marriage of the three!And now, I think I have found it! Imagine a semi-automatic 308 rifle with no gas port or operating rod to cause malfunctions over time. A lockup that is very tight, yet forgiving of debris. A "battle rifle" with FAR better accuracy than anyone has a right to expect! Magazines are cheap, reliable and readily available. I looked at and tried every proven design in the under $3,000 range; all of them wanting, except this one. Some were more accurate at the cost of reliabilty or ruggedness; but none were more reliable. And for me, reliability in all conditions is paramount. I have 3 of these rifles and will keep one for myself; this one is up for sale and will now fund my 308 "habit". Once you discover the genius in the Roller-Locked design, you will forego the "Black Rifle Disease".STAINLESS STEEL HK91 CLONE.Comes with 3-9X40 scope bore sighted.PSG-1 too expensive? Ever wish you could have a super accurate roller-locked rifle in 308? Well here's your chance! A cast Stainless receiver is VERY stiff and won't need the "T"-rails added on like the stamped steel sniper HK rifles require. Only 500 of these made. Bolt and cocking tube gap are in spec; no "ground bolt". Comes with 2 mags. Upgrades so far: G3 stock and buffer, Bill Springfield trigger job. HK91 rubber coated charging handle. I DON'T SHIP!
